import ResearchLean.AG.QualitySurface.SemanticRepairLawEquationRealization

/-!
G-06 end-to-end grounded comparison packet on the law-equation realization.

Cycle 348/349 generated the displayed required-law restriction evaluator and
the generated-Cech `sourceC0CechZero` from law-as-equation geometry, and fixed
a concrete nondegenerate instance.  This file composes that route with the
Cycle 332 canonical-argument-free grounded-packet route, producing a single
end-to-end theorem from the law-equation defect source to the selected
comparison packet: gate realization layer, degree-wise carrier data and
explicit face-restriction equations, cover-relative cochain realization, the
semantic-additive-`H1`-to-cover-relative-`H1` comparison package, residual
boundary, and the semantic / additive `H1` zero readings.

The composition is honest about where the law semantics enters: the displayed
interpretation realization conjunct consumes `displayedRequiredLawsHoldOn`
through the Cycle 348 vanishing theorem, so the base-restricted primitive of
the packet source provably realizes the law-equation source's own displayed
interpretations.  The current-G06 input surface built here carries the
ambient `G.quotientIsSheaf` (discharged for the concrete finite-model
instance, discharge-required in general) and a descent field derived from it;
no conclusion-shaped field is introduced.
-/

noncomputable section

universe u v w x y z r a b

